OL,3,CYoung muslims 'scared' to walk the
OL,4,Cstreets after riots
OL,6,F"Of course they can empathise with how
OL,7,Fyou're feeling, but they can't
OL,8,Factually put themselves in your shoes
OL,9,Fbecause they don't feel this day to
OL,10,Fday.
OL,12,F"We experience it - we see it - you
OL,13,Fcan see the stares on the tram when
OL,14,Fyou're going from point A to point B -
OL,15,Fyou can feel the voices in your head
OL,16,Fconstantly telling you what if
OL,17,Fsomething goes wrong?"
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
